The paper deals with resource planning and scheduling in a cloud computing environment, which falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The use of Hive and Pig for querying and analysis of big data suggests a focus on Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science (cs.CE). The study of workloads and arrival patterns also suggests a focus on Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). The use of statistical analysis techniques such as K-means clustering and analysis of distribution suggests a focus on Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) and Machine Learning (cs.LG).
